{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 20 g butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add 20 g honey and white chocolate then melt <b>10 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, wet and wring out a sheet of baking paper and line a rectangular tray.","Add 50 g puffed rice and mix <b>1 min\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer mixture to prepared tray.","Using the back of a spoon, level the mixture tightly to a height of 1 cm then place in fridge for 30 minutes while making chocolate layer.","Place remaining 30 g butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add remaining 30 g honey and milk chocolate then melt <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add remaining puffed rice then mix <b>1 min\/\/speed 1<b>. Allow mixture to cool in mixing bowl for 10 minutes.","Take milk chocolate mixture and spread onto white chocolate layer, leveling with back of a spoon. Place in fridge to set for 1 hour.","Remove from fridge and leave at room temperature for 10 minutes. Cut into 10 fingers with a large knife.","Pack in an airtight container ready for your picnic."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g butter, diced","50 g honey","100 g white chocolate, small pieces or callets","100 g puffed rice","150 g milk chocolate, small pieces or callets"]}],"id":"r126419","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-xrJoaENX8wY\/XZarCybsdjI\/AAAAAAAAhkU\/CSRw3nM59jkMc4Ntft_jziSCmds2NXM-wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zAQbCQuyc8YNeQhE.png","title":"Chocolate Puffed Rice Cakes","publishedAt":"2016-06-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.6 g","fat":"11.9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"27.5 g","calories":"952 kJ \/ 228 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, long sharp knife, airtight jar or container, refrigerator","basicInfo":["easy","15m","2h 35m","10 pieces"]}